commentary: On PAM 42382 and 43269, there is an additional fragment which contains more of the lamed. We have no reason to doubt this smaller join. So, we read a lamed here.

On PAM 42382 and 43269, there is the right upper stroke of the final mem. Thus, we can read עולם. We have not included it here because the small fragment, evident in the PAMs, is now lost in the IAA image.
The shape of the left ascender is odd for a heh. There appears some sort of damage, but it does not appear as though the scribe was changing the letter for any reason.
